# Feature Branch Workflow

Develop features one at a time. Each feature gets its own branch and pull request to `main`.

## Before starting work

1. Ensure `main` is up to date: `git checkout main && git pull`
2. Create a branch from `main`: `git checkout -b feature/<short-description>`
   - Examples: `feature/hold-color-sampling`, `feature/wall-highlighting`

## During development

- Keep the branch focused on **one feature** — no unrelated changes
- Run checks locally before pushing:
  ```sh
  npm run lint
  npm run typecheck
  ```
- Commit with clear messages describing the feature

## When the feature is ready

1. Push the branch: `git push -u origin feature/<short-description>`
2. Open a PR to `main` — CI runs automatically on the PR
3. Wait for CI to pass (ESLint + TypeScript)
4. Merge the PR when ready
5. Delete the branch after merge

## Starting the next feature

Always branch from updated `main`, never from another feature branch:

```sh
git checkout main
git pull
git checkout -b feature/<next-feature>
```
